IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: SEE SCHEDULE O.THE INTERNATIONAL FRESH PRODUCE ASSOCIATION IS THE LARGEST AND MOST DIVERSE INTERNATIONAL ASSOCIATION SERVING THE ENTIRE FRESH PRODUCE AND FLORAL SUPPLY CHAIN, AND THE ONLY ASSOCIATION TO SEAMLESSLY INTEGRATE WORLD-FACING ADVOCACY AND INDUSTRY-FACING SUPPORT. WE EXIST TO CREATE A VIBRANT FUTURE FOR ALL, AND TO DO SO WITH THE PRODUCE AND FLORAL INDUSTRY PROSPERITY IN MIND.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE MISSION OF THE INTERNATIONAL FRESH PRODUCE ASSOCIATION IS TO ENSURE A MEETING PLACE FOR INDUSTRY MEMBERS, CUSTOMERS, SUPPLIES AND GROUPS TO EXCHANGE IDEAS AND TO NETWORK; TO PROMOTE TO GOVERNMENT AND THE MEDIA THE INTERESTS OF SELLERS OF COMMERCIAL QUANTITIES OF FRESH FRUITS AND VEGETABLES AND FLORAL PRODUCTS; TO EDUCATE THE PUBLIC BY PROMOTING THE BENEFITS OF INCREASED CONSUMPTION OF FRESH FRUITS AND VEGETABLES, AS WELL AS THE AESTHETIC BENEFITS OF FLORAL PRODUCTS; AND, TO ASSISTE MEMBERS AND THEIR EMPLOYEES TO ENHANCE THEIR PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT.
IRS990.Desc: THE GLOBAL PRODUCE AND FLORAL SHOW - 20,000 ATTENDEES. THE SHOWS' MAIN OBJECTIVE IS TO INCREASE GLOBAL PRODUCE AND FLORAL CONSUMPTION BY CREATING A COMMUNITY OF NEW IDEAS AND NEW CONNECTIONS. THE GLOBAL PRODUCE & FLORAL SHOW CONNECTS GLOBAL SUPPLY CHAIN PARTNERS, INFORMING THEM OF THE LATEST IN CONSUMER, BUSINESS, AND INDUSTRY TRENDS, AND PROVIDING A FORUM TO DEVELOP BUSINESS SOLUTIONS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: MEMBER RELATIONS - 3000 COMPANY MEMBERS IFPA, AS A VERTICALLY INTEGRATED INTERNATIONAL TRADE ASSOCIATION THAT HAS A VERY DIVERSE MEMBERSHIP BASE WITH MEMBERS REPRESENTING 46 DIFFERENT COUNTRIES AROUND THE WORLD AND ALL SEGMENTS OF THE SUPPLY CHAIN.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: FOOD SERVICE CONFERENCE - 2,600+ ATTENDEES FOOD SERVICE CONFERENCE IS IFPA'S SECOND CONFERENCE, TO PROVIDE ACCESS TO IMPORTANT INDUSTRY INFORMATION AND OPPORTUNITIES TO CONNECT TO GROW MEMBERS' PROSPERITY. THE FOOD SERVICE CONFERENCE ASPIRES TO BE AN EVENT FOR THE BROADER FOOD SERVICE INDUSTRY. IN 2022, MANY FOOD SERVICE OPERATORS, DISTRIBUTORS, AND GROWERS' BUSINESSES HAVE BEEN LEFT IN A CRITICAL STATE, SO FOODSERVICE CONFERENCE IS OFFERED COMPLIMENTARY TO PROVIDE ACCESS TO BUSINESS CONNECTIONS AND ENGAGEMENT WITH IMPORTANT INDUSTRY TOPICS TO MOVE THE INDUSTRY FORWARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION FOLLOWS THE AUTHORITATIVE GUIDANCE RELATING TO ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES INCLUDED IN FASB ACCOUNTING STANDARDS CODIFICATION TOPIC 740, INCOME TAXES. THESE PROVISIONS PROVIDE CONSISTENT GUIDANCE FOR THE ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES RECOGNIZED IN AN ENTITY'S CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND PRESCRIBE A THRESHOLD OF "MORE LIKELY THAN NOT" FOR RECOGNITION AND DERECOGNITION OF TAX POSITIONS TAKEN OR EXPECTED TO BE TAKEN IN A TAX RETURN. IT IS THE ORGANIZATION'S POLICY TO RECOGNIZE INTEREST AND/OR PENALTIES RELATED TO UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES, IF ANY, IN INCOME TAX OR INTEREST EXPENSE. AS OF DECEMBER 31, 2022, THE ORGANIZATION HAD NO ACCRUED INTEREST AND/OR PENALTIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GENERAL MEMBERSHIP ELIGIBILITY. GENERAL MEMBERSHIP IS FOR THOSE INDIVIDUALS, FIRMS, ASSOCIATIONS OR CORPORATIONS ENGAGED IN THE MARKETING OF PRODUCE AND FLORAL PRODUCTS OR PROVIDING EQUIPMENT, MATERIALS, TRANSPORTATION, TECHNOLOGY OR OTHER SERVICES TO THESE INDUSTRIES, WHO MEET ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA ESTIABLISHED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. EACH GENERAL MEMBER SHALL HAVE THE RIGHT TO CAST ONE VOTE ON ALL MATTERS SUBMITTED TO THE MEMBERSHIP. OTHER MEMBERSHIP CATEGORIES. LIFE MEMBERSHIP WITHOUT VOTING RIGHTS MAY BE CONFERRED UPON INDIVIDUALS UNDER TERMS THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS DETERMINES. OTHER MEMBERSHIP CATEGORIES MAY BE ESTABLISHED TO MEET CHANGING INDUSTRY NEEDS BASED ON CRITERIA DETERMINED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FOR THE PERIOD FROM INCORPORATION UNTIL JANUARY 1, 2023, THE ELECTIVE OFFICERS OF THE ASSOCIATION SHALL APPOINT TWO CO-CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICERS, ONE OF WHICH SHALL BE DESIGNATED TO SERVE UNTIL JANUARY 1, 2024, AND THE OTHER OF WHICH SHALL BE DESIGNATED TO SERVE UNTIL THE NEXT ANNUAL BOARD OF DIRECTORS MEETING AFTER AN ANNIVERSARY OF INCORPORATION. AFTER THIS INITIAL TERM, A CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER MAY BE REAPPOINTED TO SUCCESSIVE TERMS WITHOUT LIMITATION. IN THE EVENT A NON-OFFICER MEMBER OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS RESIGNS OR IS UNABLE TO CONTINUE TO SERVE FOR ANY REASON BEFORE THE EXPIRATION OF ELIGIBILITY FOR CONSECUTIVE-TERM SERVICE, A SUCCESSOR MAY BE APPOINTED BY THE CHAIR TO SERVE UNTIL THE NEXT OCCURRING REGULAR ELECTION FOR THAT BOARD SEAT ACCORDING TO ITS CLASS. NO DIRECTOR MAY BE APPOINTED TO COMPLETE THE TERM OF ANOTHER DIRECTOR MORE THAN ONCE UNLESS THAT APPOINTED DIRECTOR FILLS THAT VACANCY AT LEAST ONE YEAR AFTER THE APPOINTED DIRECTOR'S PREVIOUS SERVICE ON THE BOARD.
